ons|2009]]\n|{{composition bar|12|17|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|289|587|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|121|211|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|[[Ma Ying-jeou]]\n|-\n![[2006 Taiwanese local elections|2006]]<br />{{small|municipalities only}}\n|{{composition bar|1|2|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|41|96|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|[[Ma Ying-jeou]]\n|-\n![[2005 Taiwanese local elections|2005]]\n|{{composition bar|14|23|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|408|901|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|173|319|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|[[Ma Ying-jeou]]\n|-\n![[2002 Taiwanese local elections|2002]]<br />{{small|municipalities only}}\n|{{composition bar|1|2|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|32|96|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|[[Lien Chan]]\n|-\n![[2001 Taiwanese local elections|2001]]\n|{{composition bar|9|23|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|382|897|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|195|319|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|[[Lien Chan]]\n|-\n![[1998 Taiwanese municipal elections|1998]]<br />{{small|municipalities only}}\n|{{composition bar|1|2|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|48|96|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|[[Lee Teng-hui]]\n|-\n![[1997 Taiwanese local elections|1997]]\n|{{composition bar|8|23|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|522|886|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|236|319|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|[[Lee Teng-hui]]\n|-\n![[1994 Taiwanese municipal elections|1994]]<br />{{small|province-level only}}\n|{{composition bar|2|3|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|91|175|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|[[Lee Teng-hui]]\n|}\n\n=== National Assembly elections ===\n{|class=wikitable\n!Election\n!Total seats won\n!Total votes\n!Share of votes\n!Changes\n!Party leader\n!Status\n!President\n|-\n![[2005 Taiwan National Assembly election|2005]]\n|{{composition bar|117|300|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|1,508,384\n|38.92%\n|{{decrease}} 66 seats\n|[[Lien Chan]]\n|{{partial|Plurality}}\n|\n|-\n![[1991 Taiwan National Assembly election|1991]]\n|{{composition bar|254|325|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|6,053,366\n|69.1%\n|{{increase}} 186 seats\n|[[Lee Teng-hui]]\n|{{yes|Majority}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Lee Teng-hui]] {{KMT/logo}}\n|-\n![[1996 Taiwan National Assembly election|1996]]\n|{{composition bar|183|334|hex={{Kuomintang/meta/color}}}}\n|5,180,829\n|49.7%\n|{{decrease}} 71 seats\n|[[Lee Teng-hui]]\n|{{yes|Majority}}\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Conservatism|Taiwan|China|Politics}}\n* [[Administrative divisions of the Republic of China]]\n* [[February 28 Incident]]\n* [[Campaign at the China\u2013Burma border]]\n* [[Chinese nationalism]]\n* [[Conservatism in Taiwan]]\n* [[Elections in Taiwan]]\n* [[Index of Taiwan-related articles]]\n* [[History of the Kuomintang cultural policy]]\n* [[History of the Republic of China]]\n* [[Joseph Stilwell#Disagreements with Chiang and the Allies|Joseph Stilwell]]\n* [[KMT retreat to Taiwan in 1949]]\n* [[Kuomintang Islamic insurgency in China (1950\u201358)]]\n* [[Military of the Republic of China]]\n* [[National Revolutionary Army]]\n* [[Nationalist government]]\n* [[New Kuomintang Alliance]]\n* [[Political status of Taiwan]]\n* [[Politics of the Republic of China]]\n* [[Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang]]\n* [[Outline of Taiwan]]\n* [[Whampoa Military Academy]]\n* [[White Terror (Taiwan)]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n=== Words in native languages ===\n{{notelist-ur}}\n\n== References ==\n=== Citations ===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n=== Sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |first2=Janet |last2=Lloyd |last1=Bergere |first1=Marie-Claire |title